<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Channel Seven's new military-style reality show SAS Australia will see stars attempt to pass the selection process to join the Australian Army's elite Special Air Service.</p>

<p>And in a trailer released on Sunday, former Ironwoman Candice Warner revealed her daughters Ivy Mae, six, Indi Rae, four, and Isla, one, are what inspired her to sign on. </p>

<p>The 35-year-old said she wanted to remind her young children shared with cricket star husband David Warner, that 'it's not just daddy who is tough and strong'.</p>

<p>Not just a WAG: Candice Warner (pictured standing), 35, said she's 'just as tough and strong' as her cricket star husband David Warner, in a new trailer for Seven's military-style reality show SAS Australia, released on Sunday </p>

<p>In the trailer, an emotional Candice announced on camera that she's not just a cricket WAG. </p>

<p>'I'm doing this for my family to show my kids that it's not just daddy who is tough and strong,' she said.  </p>

<p>The mother-of-two is seen gritting her teeth as she embarked on a set of gruelling challenges, led by former British soldier Ant Middleton.  </p>

<p>Her motivation: 'I'm doing this for my family to show my kids that it's not just daddy who is tough and strong,' the former Ironwoman said </p>

<p>Sporting power couple: Candice is pictured with David, 33, who she wed in 2015 </p>

<p>Family: They share three daughters, Ivy Mae, six, Indi Rae, four, and Isla, one (all pictured) </p>

<p>Two new recruits were also introduced in the trailer: former Miss Universe Australia Erin McNaught and Jackson Warne, the son of cricket star Shane Warne. </p>

<p>'I'm doing this for the boys,' Erin, 38, said, referencing her sons Evander, five, and Ennio, two, shared with English rapper husband Example.</p>

<p>She continued: 'I'm not just the mum that packs their lunches, I'm much more than that, as every mother is.' </p>

<p>Signed on: Two new recruits were also introduced in the trailer: former Miss Universe Australia Erin McNaught (pictured) and Jackson Warne, the son of cricket star Shane Warne </p>

<p>Inspiration: 'I'm doing this for the boys,' Erin, 38, said, referencing her sons Evander, five, and Ennio, two, shared with English rapper husband Example </p>

<p>Jackson also announced on camera that he's more than just celebrity offspring.</p>

<p>'I'm not just Shane Warne's son, I'm tougher than that. I want him to be really proud of me,' the 20-year-old said.   </p>

<p>SAS Australia is a remake of the hit British TV show SAS: Who Dares Wins.</p>

<p>Star father: Jackson (pictured) also announced on camera that he's more than just celebrity offspring</p>

<p>Making his father proud: 'I'm not just Shane Warne's son, I'm tougher than that. I want him to be really proud of me,' the 20-year-old said </p>

<p>Alongside Candice, Erin and Jackson, other stars confirmed include convicted drug smuggler Schapelle Corby, publicist Roxy Jacenko and radio star Merrick Watts. </p>

<p>Filming began earlier this year in Queenstown, New Zealand, however, it resumed in the Snowy Mountains, New South Wales, due to strict international travel restrictions amid the coronavirus pandemic. </p>

<p>SAS Australia premieres this October on Channel Seven. </p>

<p>Cast: Other stars confirmed include convicted drug smuggler Schapelle Corby (pictured) and publicist Roxy Jacenko. It premieres on Seven in October</p>
